President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate Morse H. Tan of Illinois as the Ambassador at Large for Global Criminal Justice. Mr. Tan is currently an Associate Professor and Professor of Law at Northern Illinois University College of Law. He has previously held positions at Florida Coastal School of Law, University of St. Thomas, and Handong International Law School in South Korea. Mr. Tan has completed the Emerging Leader program of the Chicago Council on Global Affairs and has been recognized as Korean-American of the Year by the Korean-American Society of Chicago. He holds a B.A. and M.A. from Wheaton College and a J.D. from Northwestern University Pritzker School of Law, specializing in international law. He is fluent in Korean and Spanish.